    "description": "HYPER Inc. engaged in the IT services and computer business in Japan. The company supplies a range of office PC and provides implementation plan and support, equipment procurement, operational support, and collect services. It also designs, installs, and configures various servers, installs and configures client PC, builds network, and performs kitting works; and provides IT infrastructure installation and configuration services and other construction work. The company sells, installs, and maintains communication, office, and office automation equipment; plans, develops, and sells software; and provides information processing services. In addition, the company is involved in the planning and production of websites; content management system development; designs and produces company brochures, pamphlets, posters, business cards, and various promotional tools; internet mail ordering business; and network construction, system maintenance, and digital content production services. The company operates Sasumaru that provides an ordering and contract management platform for SaaS products, mainly Microsoft 365 and ZOOM; HYPER FACTORY, an online store that handles business-use products, including printers, multifunction devices, and uninterruptible power supplies; a security platform under the Securitya brand; and media outlets, such as HYPER Voice that provides information on corporate IT trends and solutions to problems, and Cloud Infobox for work style reform and cloud services information that are useful for management, as well as operates the Askul Agent business, a mail-order business platform. In addition, it offers maintenance and IT consulting services, as well as specialized services comprising software development, maintenance, implementation, and operation. Further, the company sells office supplies, office furniture, etc. HYPER Inc. was incorporated in 1990 and is headquartered in Chuo, Japan."
